Two men, Afeez Adegboyega and Ismaila Hamzat, yesterday appeared at an Ebute Meta Magistrates’ Court, Lagos, for allegedly stealing 81 bags of cocoa valued at N6.4 million. Adegboyega, 26, and Hamzat, 34, who are facing trial for conspiracy and stealing, however, pleaded innocence. Prosecuting Inspector Jimah Iseghede alleged that the defendants committed the offences on January 4, at Costain, Lagos. He said the defendants, who were assigned to deliver the goods worth N6.4 million,  belonging to Olam Nigeria Ltd., could not account for how they got missing. Iseghede said the offences contravened sections 287 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. Magistrate Mrs. A.O. Salawu admitted the defendants to N500, 000 bail with two sureties each in the like sum. The case continues on May 22. 